      "id": "assistant-1775142320144-h63pvr",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "I turned this into a six-shot storyboard that leans into the fake-historical-thriller setup, then drops hard into the library reveal.\n\nThe shape is:\n\n1. urgent departure on the donkey  \n2. weaving through market congestion  \n3. wider Florence scale with the Duomo under construction  \n4. frantic arrival and dismount  \n5. hard-cut reveal: overdue book at the library desk  \n6. final donkey-through-the-window flower-eating button\n\nWhat’s working creatively is the progression of scale:\n- start personal and stressed\n- expand into civic grandeur\n- hit peak urgency at the doorway\n- then collapse into stillness and embarrassment\n\nThe next move is to generate the storyboard board and review it before we lock keyframes."
    },
