    {
      "id": "assistant-1775153796943-z4rh4y",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Done — the keyframe prompts are now written for all 7 planned anchors.\n\nThe set is shaped to preserve continuity while sharpening the joke:\n- **SHOT-01** establishes the merchant’s panic and the donkey’s calm\n- **SHOT-02** intensifies the chaos in the market\n- **SHOT-03** opens into the epic Duomo backdrop\n- **SHOT-04 START / END** gives the arrival beat a real visual escalation\n- **SHOT-05** hard-resets into the quiet library reveal\n- **SHOT-06** lands the flower-eating donkey button\n\nI kept the still prompts grounded and image-model friendly: clear subject focus, readable staging, strong period detail, and continuity references to the character sheets and prior frames where that helps.\n\nNext move: generate the keyframe images and review them before we treat these anchors as locked. Once those renders are in, I can help you do a fast taste pass on:\n- character consistency\n- whether the Duomo shot feels grand enough\n- whether the library reveal cuts hard enough\n- whether the final donkey gag reads instantly"
